				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm of the opinion that it's better to leave NMIs always on and control what happens each vblank entirely in software. You can even use the shadow $2001 register to detect when rendering is off, in which case the vblank handler skips all code related to the PPU (after updating register $2001 with the shadow value, that is), so it doesn't interfere with any PPU operations the main thread may be doing (e.g. large updates between levels), but still updates the APU so that music and sound effects aren't interrupted by screen transitions.</div>

