				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The function of the colon is described in <a href="https://cc65.github.io/doc/ca65.html#ss6.6" class="postlink">ca65 Users Guide: Unnamed labels</a>. The <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">+</tt> goes on the same line as the <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">:</tt>, not on the next line.<br /><br />This code:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">inc ptr,x<br />bne :+<br />&nbsp; inc ptr+1,x<br />:<br /></div><br /><br />Is equivalent to this code:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">inc ptr,x<br />bne @ptr_hi_does_not_need_to_be_incremented<br />&nbsp; inc ptr+1,x<br />@ptr_hi_does_not_need_to_be_incremented:<br /></div></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
