				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In ASM6 that'd be:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">inc ptr,x<br />bne +<br />&nbsp; inc ptr+1,x<br />+<br /></div><br />+ (plus) is for forward references, - (minus) is for backward references. If you need more than one unnamed label in the same area you can use ++, +++, and so on.<br /><br />You shouldn't use these types of labels too much, otherwise your code can get really confusing. I only use unnamed labels for really short jumps and in the same &quot;logic block&quot;.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

