					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I guess you already know this, tokumaru, but I use unnamed labels most of the time.  They really help with padding!  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br /><tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">+jDS</tt> means to me that the label is only branched to from &lt; #$81 bytes before the label.   <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">+jDS jmp DrawSprite</tt> is paddable afterwards because everything reaching it will jump to DrawSprite. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

